How to make yourself more valuable

First， Accumulation
Study, delve into → Acquire skills, experiences and experiences that most people do not have → People around me ask me or recommend me to others → Be noticed by more people;

Second, focus on valuable things
  a. Market demand: what are the companies doing, what are the problems → solve technical problems and improve team efficiency;
  b. Technology trends: understand history, technology development trajectory ∈ new technologies; Looking at the development of technology on the timeline in history, you will understand what tomorrow's technology will look like.
    I: What problem does it solve, and why can't similar technologies do it?
    II: Why is it solved this way? Is there a better way?
    iii: The more support from large commercial companies behind new technologies, the more attention needs to be paid to.
  
Third, find a place that reflects value: tell the company that develops.

Fourth, hands-on ability is very important, at least knock on whether to understand the details.

Fifth, pay attention to technical payment points: can help others make money; Can help others save money (improve efficiency, save costs).

Sixth,Improve ability and experience: do core projects in well-known companies.

Seventh,Find valuable sources: Google + English.

Eighth, Export views and values. Think about why this is the case, and not that, and draw inferences.




